Route timeout test (45-second expiration).

Tests:
1) Route learning via neighbor
2) Route expiration when updates stop
3) DATA packet failure when no route exists

Expected behavior:
- Node 1 initially learns route to node 3 via node 2
- At t=50s, link (2,3) dies
- Node 2 stops advertising route to node 3
- Node 1's route to node 3 expires ~45 seconds after last update
- At t=100s, DATA packet from 1 to 3 should fail (no valid route)

This test verifies the 45-second route timeout requirement from
Section 4.2 of the specification.
